item.g:title: Bookish Goals Planner Junk Journal Kit with Ephemera
item.g:description: 20 pages junk journal kit featuring blue blush color palette florals, books and bookish quotes. Can be used for junk journaling, scrapbooking or other art and crafts projects. PRODUCT KIT INCLUDES: - 10 Foldable Journal Pages - Mix of elaborately decorated and plain journal pages for writing and decoupage. Includes 2 Foldable Planner Pages: Bookish Goals, Bookish Goals Review. (Print multiple times for each month. Undated, reusable planner pages.) - 2 Textured Digital Papers to Print on Back of Ephemera. 1 Lined, 1 Unlined. - 8 Pages of Ephemera: Quote Cards, Labels, Pockets, Corner Pockets, Tall Tags, Rounded Tags, Shape Tags, Journal Cards, Bookmarks, Tuck Bands, Washi Tapes. ******************** THIS IS A DIGITAL PRODUCT. NO PHYSICAL PRODUCT WILL BE SHIPPED. PLEASE READ DETAILED DESCRIPTION! No shipping hassles. After payment you will be taken to the download page and an email will be sent to you with your download link. You need to download, print and craft your own junk journal. ******************** Terms of Use You MAY download, print and craft from the printable files as many times as you want, FOR PERSONAL, NON-COMMERCIAL USE ONLY. You MAY NOT reproduce, duplicate, copy, sell, resell or exploit any portion of the products for any other purpose. ******************** TIPS Basic crafting/ junk journaling skills can be learned from the many tutorial videos out there on Youtube. Bookbinding can be done using simple sewing, tying the journal pages with a ribbon, punching holes in the pages and using a ring binder, etc. PRINTING Print on standard letter size (8.5x11) paper or cardstock, in landscape orientation. Unless you have a borderless printer, your printed journal page will have white margins around the print, which you will need to cut to prepare your journal pages. Final pages will measure approximately 5x8 inches when folded, depending on your margin settings. MIX and MATCH You can mix and match the order of the pages. Print a journal page on one side of the paper or cardstock, flip and feed the paper through the printer to print another journal page on the other side. ⭐ Download and DIY Print – Please refer to how to print tips for more information on downloading and printing. ******************** Due to differences in monitors and printers, colors may vary slightly. Final print quality will also depend on factors such as type of printer and paper. ❤️Thanks for visiting, please message me for any other queries.
